          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search          von Hardenberg is a German surname. Notable people with the surname include:  Karl August von Hardenberg (1750–1822), Prussian statesman Georg Philipp Friedrich Freiherr von Hardenberg (1772–1801), German poet known as Novalis Carl-Hans Graf von Hardenberg (1891–1958), German politician Astrid Gräfin von Hardenberg (1925–2015)  See also[edit]  Hardenberg (disambiguation) Hardenbergh Hardenburg (disambiguation)      This page or section lists people with the surname von Hardenberg. If an internal link intending to refer to a specific person led you to this page, you may wish to change that link by adding the person's given name(s) to the link.                      Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Von_Hardenberg&oldid=721998791"          Categories: SurnamesGerman-language surnamesHidden categories: All set index articles            
